- "planted seeds worth more than 500 units" refers to the total amount of completed income transactions greater than 500.0;
- "fertile soil of completed income transactions of type 0" refers to transactions where the transaction type ID is 0, is_income is 1, and the status is 'completed'.

- 'Flowers of savings accounts' refers to transactions in savings accounts;
- 'Blooms' represent the transactions;
- 'Petals' represent individual transactions;
- 'Bloom type' (income or expense) refers to the `is_income` column;
